"{\"uid\": \"smh.com.au-national-mossad-chief-who-led-hunt-to-kill-perpetrators-of-munich-olympic-massacre-dies-at-98-20240103-p5euxv.html\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are sorry, this feature is currently unavailable.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this feature\", \"from\": 14, \"to\": 26}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are working to restore it.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again later.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was published1yearago Add articles to your saved list and come back to them any time.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"articles\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 147}, {\"ngram\": \"your saved list\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zvi Zamir, who has died aged 98, was a general in the Israel Defence Forces before becoming Director of Mossad, Israel's intelligence agency, in 1968; in this capacity he led Operation Wrath of God to hunt and kill those responsible for theMunich Massacre.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zvi Zamir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Israel Defence Forces\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.355105899703544e-26, \"text\": \"Wrath\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a general\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 247}, {\"ngram\": \"Director\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"this capacity\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 368}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 398}, {\"ngram\": \"theMunich Massacre\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On September 5, 1972, eight heavily armed militants from Black September, a faction of the PLO, stormed the building housing the Israeli delegation to the Munich Olympic Games, killing two athletes and taking nine hostages; they demanded the release of 236 Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.524999640870191e-85, \"text\": \"PLO\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Munich Olympic Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 4.780565661060407e-13, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 746, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"eight heavily armed militants\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 510}, {\"ngram\": \"Black September\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 531}, {\"ngram\": \"a faction\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"two athletes\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"nine hostages\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"the release\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 708}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government, led by Prime Minister Golda Meir, declined to cave in, and Meir handed responsibility for the crisis to her trusted Mossad chief.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Golda Meir\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The government\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"Meir\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"responsibility\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the crisis\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A still of Zamir from the 1999 documentaryOne Day in September, which detailed the events of the 1972 Munich massacre.Credit:Alamy Zamir rushed to Munich, where he pleaded with West German officials to permit Sayeret Matkal - at that time one of the few military units trained in hostage rescue and counterterrorism - to rescue the Israeli athletes.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 1056, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1999 documentaryOne Day\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"September\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"the events\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"Alamy\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"West German officials\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"Sayeret Matkal\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"the few military units\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"hostage rescue\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"counterterrorism\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as the German constitution prohibited foreigners from carrying out military operations on German soil, his request was rejected.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999979689712453, \"rank\": 2.031033184265457e-06, \"text\": \"German constitution\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999922481938804, \"rank\": 7.75185654839888e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"foreigners\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1311}, {\"ngram\": \"military operations\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"his request\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hijackers demanded two helicopters to fly them and their hostages to the nearby F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck airfield, and a special plane to take them from there to an Arab country.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.809565172680818e-17, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The hijackers\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1406}, {\"ngram\": \"two helicopters\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"their hostages\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1462}, {\"ngram\": \"the nearby F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck airfield\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"a special plane\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Germans agreed and planned to use snipers to shoot the hijackers when they transferred from the helicopters to the plane.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"snipers\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1613}, {\"ngram\": \"the hijackers\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1636}, {\"ngram\": \"the helicopters\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1679}, {\"ngram\": \"the plane\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1692}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir, who was flown to F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck just ahead of the terrorists and their hostages, watched with growing frustration as the Germans prepared themselves for the showdown.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"score\": 0.9255849604882891, \"rank\": 0.06460625109127516, \"text\": \"F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"the terrorists\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"their hostages\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"growing frustration\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1817}, {\"ngram\": \"the showdown\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Germans were useless \\u2026 useless all the way,\\\" he recalled.\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1876, \"end\": 1883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was pitch black at the airport, and the artificial light was patently inadequate for a sniping operation.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the airport\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1968}, {\"ngram\": \"the artificial light\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"a sniping operation\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2042}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Worse, only five snipers were allocated the task of tackling eight terrorists; several of the snipers' guns were not fitted with telescopic sights, and the snipers, deployed approximately 100 metres away from their commanders, were not issued with means of communication to co-ordinate their firing.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only five snipers\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"the task\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"eight terrorists\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2121}, {\"ngram\": \"the snipers' guns\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"telescopic sights\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"the snipers\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"their commanders\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2269}, {\"ngram\": \"means\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"communication\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"their firing\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2342}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Palestinian terrorist holds members of the Israeli Olympic team hostage at their quarters at the Munich athletes' village in 1972.Credit:AP When the snipers opened fire they failed to kill all the hijackers in the first volley and a gunfight ensued.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 4.780565661060407e-13, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Israeli Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"their quarters\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"1972.Credit\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"AP\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"the snipers\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2503}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"all the hijackers\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"the first volley\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2573}, {\"ngram\": \"a gunfight\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The three remaining terrorists tossed hand grenades into one of the helicopters; the explosion ignited the fuel tank and the handcuffed Israelis still sitting inside were burnt alive.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The three remaining terrorists\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"hand grenades\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"the helicopters\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2677}, {\"ngram\": \"the explosion\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"the fuel tank\", \"from\": 2701, \"to\": 2714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another hijacker sprayed the Israelis in the other helicopter with bullets.\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another hijacker\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2798}, {\"ngram\": \"the other helicopter\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2843}, {\"ngram\": \"bullets\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir, witnessing the disaster from the control tower, insisted on getting out to the balcony to negotiate with the terrorists.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2864}, {\"ngram\": \"the disaster\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"the control tower\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"the balcony\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2952}, {\"ngram\": \"the terrorists\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taking with him an Arabic-speaking aide, Zamir used a megaphone to shout: \\\"Stop firing \\u2026 the plane is ready for you \\u2026 STOP FIRING\\\".\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Arabic-speaking aide\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3026}, {\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3033}, {\"ngram\": \"a megaphone\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"the plane\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3085}, {\"ngram\": \"FIRING\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But, as he recalled, \\\"Their reply was clear \\u2026 they opened fire at us on the balcony.\\\"\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their reply\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3181}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3187}, {\"ngram\": \"the balcony\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back at the Olympic Village, Zamir telephoned Meir at home in Israel.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3268, \"end\": 3274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Village\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3240}, {\"ngram\": \"Meir\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Golda, I have got bad news,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bad news\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just back from the airport \\u2026 not one of the Israelis has survived.\\\"\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the airport\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a later interview, Zamir said: \\\"To see this happen on German soil was a terrible sight.\\\"\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999922481938804, \"rank\": 7.75185654839888e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a later interview\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3409}, {\"ngram\": \"Zamir\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"a terrible sight\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3478}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The aftermath of the events at F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck airfield in 1972,Credit:Fairfax archive Zvi Zamir was born Zvicka Zarzev